Package com.ibm.security.verifysdk

Class VerifySdkException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • com.ibm.security.verifysdk.VerifySdkException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    @RequiresApi(23)
public class VerifySdkException
extends java.lang.Exception
    The customized exception class. It provides the original cause if applicable (see below), an ErrorCode and description and data that is relevant to the cause.

    It has two uses cases:

    • in callbacks (see IResultCallback and ITransactionResultCallback) to represent the error that might has occurred.
    • as a wrapper for exceptions thrown inside of the SDK other then IllegalArgumentException. These are primarily JSON related exceptions for parsing and serialization. The original cause is accessible in this class.
    Since:
    2.0.0
